About the Fund Manager
Boston Common Asset Management is an investment manager specializing in sustainable and responsible investing. Boston Common managed approximately $2.3 billion in assets as of March 31, 2017, including subadvised assets, for investors seeking diversified portfolios of long-only U.S. and International equity. With a global focus and a commitment to responsible practices, Boston Common is independent, employee-owned, and fields a seasoned team of close-knit professionals.
As a group, we value the diversity of opinions around the table and have worked to maintain an open communication structure. Our Investment Team expects excellence and seeks the highest standards. Our in-house social research and advocacy team leads the shareholder engagement initiatives that resonate with their passions and further our clients' missions. We share a firm-wide commitment to integrity and responsiveness to our clients' unique investment objectives. Boston Common is women-led and majority-employee-owned.




